rComments: Professor Sowinski is clearly passionate about what he does. This is the one class I took that felt really good online, as it was about using excel and VBA. he records his lectures which are amazing come important evaluations such as tests and exams. Nothing negative to say, just an awesome chill guy.

Professor Sowinski deserves all the praise he gets. It was a difficult semester in the middle of a pandemic but he always did his best to reach his students and make sure we all had the opportunity to succeed. Lectures could get confusing and a little messy sometimes but going over his recordings helps with that. Very nice man.

Will stop everything to help you if you need it. Great lectures, and is clearly passionate about what he is teaching. Gives many chances for success, I really recommend Prof Sowinski if you get the chance. He clearly cares about his students.
Dr. Sowinski was always incredibly detailed in his feedback regarding the lab reports, as well as always being open to answer any questions. Great professor, as usual!

Speed matters a lot, especially if in-person. So practice that a lot depending on the mode of teaching. His recorded summer videos are super useful. It really all does come down to the projects. Make sure you have at least one (med to awesome) coder in your group because project difficulty ranges from med to hard. Project results depends on them.

honestly this ANGEL of a man made the transition to online learning so nice and he cares so much about his students and he's always available to answer your questions and gives you so much good feedback

I seriously can't sing this guy's praises enough. Hands-down best prof all of first year. Material could be complicated to follow in class but he was always available in office hours and was able to clarify things every time. Also a great guy, get to know him and he'll discuss pretty much anything with you. If you have the chance, take his class!

If you solve the practice problems he gives you, which are extremely clear and concise and easy to follow, as well as the "level quizzes" on brightspace (specifically the last level quiz of each topic since the test questions are a carbon copy of those), you are guaranteed a minimum of 80% on all your tests.

He is a great prof! He is always willing to help you and wants you to answer your questions. To Sowinski you aren't just a body in a chair. You are a person who he wants to get to know. Only issue to the class is it was brand new and nobody really knows how to teach a 3rd year course to first years. Do the work, don't slack and you will be fine.

Dr. Sowinski is the best professor in chemical engineering. He is very personable and really wants students to succeed. He is always available to help students outside of class and can explain things many different ways. Gives fair exams, and spends a lot of time researching student learning.

He is a caring prof, however he fools his students. The midterm was fair the final exam was a killer. His powerpoint slides were completely useless and the way he explains them with his pointer isn't effective. He likes to make it extremely hard on his students by not posting solutions just final numbers. Very Deceiving
amazing.

WOW. Sowinski easily earns his hotness pepper. Not to mention, he's a great prof who cares about you learning the material. Solid dude with a great attitude, keeps you interested during lectures and marks fairly.

I love Sowinski! Not only is he an amazing professor, he is also always available to help as guidance. He wants his students to do well. CHG1125 can be hard for some student (aka me) and Andrew was always available after class to clarify topics and help me to study with tips on time management and how to do well overall. My favorite prof at uO.

Pathetic! His presentations were unclear with a lot of errors in formula. He rectifies the mistakes in his lectures(PPT) after long done. Finally ended up having mass confusion in what formula to use. Not fit to teach Masters level course. Not a fair grader.

Amazing prof. Makes even the dullest of subject matters interesting! Definitely recommended. You can find a free online version of the textbook without any difficulties. If you do the suggested problem sets and understand them, you should have no trouble on the quizzes. Exam was quite lengthy but pretty straight forward. Good luck!
Get the book. Show up to class.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Beware of pop quizzes']

rComments: Great professor. Very caring, genuine. Super hot.
Great guy, however his teaching style using powerpoints is quite a poor choice. He goes over content too quickly to process the information.
Awesome prof and very friendly. He has definitely improved over the years and can potentially become one of the best of the program in the future. Definitely one of my favourites. #datass

Great professor, definitely improved his teaching style significantly. Could easily tell that he followed through with student feedback given in the first year course. Very clear in his teaching and expectations, and cares about the success of his students.

This prof is a nice guy, down to earth. He is young so he will probably improve as he gains experience. The textbook saved my life because his notes can be unclear some times and problems are very similar to txtbook. He basically gives points for participation and he is not a tough grader. If you do and understand the assignments you will be ok.

had him last year for chg1125 and again this fall for chg2317. he's improved significantly in his teaching style and engages the class much more. also really reasonable and a down to earth guy who is easy to chat with about study techniques, course material, etc. Tests are easy/fair, just make sure to study literally everything.

Andrew is a great guy!. I don't like his teaching methods and honestly i didn't learn anything from the class but he is an inspiration for me, He is very clear cut and he is really helpful. If you want to know about your career, he's the guy you want to discuss with. Textbook use is a must!

Lectures are a little dry, and often times consist of him reading off the slides. While he isn't the best lecturer, he is very helpful, and incredibly clear on his expectations, giving many hints on what will be tested on. Has many interesting stories of his experiences with the industry. Overall a good professor.

Sowinski is a god among engineers. He's relatable, easy-going, & inspirational. He understands what it's like to be a first year student, and that is reflective in his teaching. The course content isn't that hard, and he's always available if you need help. He was hands-down, my best prof in first year. Not to mention, he's easy on the eyes #datass

Very laid back. Material for the course was really straight-forward -- I preferred reading the book to listening in the lectures. Lots of examples in class, clear expectations re quizzes and exams. Going to class was very helpful. Lots of hints about what would be on the tests, great stories about working as a chemical engineer.

Funny, laid-back guy. He somehow managed to put up with a lot of 247 talkers during his classes.  Gives you everything you need to know and makes you practice it. Midterm and final were marked fair. If you can do all the assignments and DGD quizes, you're guaranteed +75% in the midterm and final.

He's a very laid back prof,  and while he's not the most inspirational speaker, he knows what he's talking about and he conveys it well. There are weekly assignments and periodic quizzes, all widely varying in difficulty. The questions are manageable if you do the assignments and suggested problems. Overall a nice course with an average workload.

Teaching is simply not his thing. He just skims through slides and copies the solution manual to the textbook in class. It is very vague what he is trying to convey, and does not really show interest in teaching the subject himself. Textbooks are allowed for the midterm and final, but are only useful for their charts. Wording on exams is horrific.

Good prof. Cares about his students. He gives fair assessments (midterm,quizzes,assignments) but grades them hard, so it may or may not work in your favor... Great guy, very knowledgable about the industry, and a great person to go to for advice on anything from jobs, to graduate studies... Great dude

One of my favorite profs. Not necessarily an inspirational lecturer, but he's funny, answers questions, and always answers emails, and I genuinely enjoyed the subject matter. Homework is hard, but not impossible. Midterms and quizzes are extremely easy, but don't let that get you too cocky for the exam, which is significantly harder.
Awesome guy ! No complaints at all, midterm was easy as hell but the final was generally harder yet very possible, easier then calc 2 guys !

All he does is read off the slides, but does not actually teach. His assignments are brutal near the end, but his midterms and quizzes are not hard. He is just a very poor lecturer and seems like he is falling asleep when hes talking. He does infact, try his best not to make eye contact with his students while teaching.
Good prof. Midterm was long (not tricky), exam was more than fair (easy actually). Available via email, and willing to help students outside class

Easily the best professor I've had (4th year student). Amazingly helpful, always available by email (literally responds within minutes). Class average went up 5 letter grades when he took it over as a first time professor even though the quizzes, assignments and exam were significantly harder. He did turn down our offer to come to a rave though.

Easy course for the most part, the math is very easy to follow and his quizzes & final exam are fair. The only tough part of the course is scoring well on the assignments. The TA's are quite picky on the marking scheme and they mark based on the marking scheme too literally.

Good professor for his first time lecturing a full course. He tends to go by a little fast though. Since he recently graduated he does expect you to know quite a bit and/or adapt quickly in his classes. Likes adding small tricks in his quizzes.
